
[1]threshhold

   THRESH'HOLD, n.

   1. The door-sill; the plank, stone or piece of timber which lies at the
   bottom or under a door, particularly of a dwelling house, church,
   temple or the like; hence, entrance; gate; door.

   2. Entrance; the place or point of entering or beginning. He is now at
   the threshhold of his argument.

   Many men that stumble at the threshhold.
